SIMPLE: election
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Election
<hw>E*lec"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧lection</ets>, L. <ets>electio</ets>, fr.
<ets>eligere</ets> to choose out. See <er>Elect</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of choosing; choice;
selection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of choosing a person to fill an office, or
to membership in a society, as by ballot, uplifted hands, or <xex>viva
voce</xex>; <as>as, the <ex>election</ex> of a president or a
mayor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Corruption in <qex>elections</qex> is the great enemy of
freedom.</q> <rj><qau>J. Adams.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Power of choosing; free will; liberty to choose or
act.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧By his own <xex>election</xex> led to ill.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Daniel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Discriminating choice; discernment.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To use men with much difference and <qex>election</qex> is
good.</q> <rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>Divine choice; predestination of
individuals as objects of mercy and salvation; -- one of the ⟦ldquo⟧five
points⟦rdquo⟧ of Calvinism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There is a remnant according to the <qex>election</qex> of
grace.</q> <rj><qau>Rom. xi. 5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The choice, made by a party, of two
alternatives, by taking one of which, the chooser is excluded from the
other.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Those who are elected.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>election</qex> hath obtained it.</q> <rj><qau>Rom. xi.
7.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To contest an election</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Contest</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>To make one's election</b></col>,
<cd>to choose.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>has made his election</qex> to walk, in the main, in the
old paths.</q> <rj><qau>Fitzed. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electioneer</ent>⟦br⟧
